Sql Injection : 
Technique where an application is vulnerable to SQL injection but its HTTP responses do not contain the results of the relevant query or any database errors. 
Attackers extract data by asking the database true/false questions or by forcing time delays.

Description: Sqli blind where output is not shown in http request but retrieved via automation.

Difficulty Level: medium CWE ID: CWE-89 (SQL Injection) CVSS Score: 9.0 (Critical) Risk Rating: Critical

Impact: Data extraction and enumeration possible without visible output.
